timeline.body:
It is better practice to write:
```java
if (definitelyNotNull.equals(possiblyNull)) {
    // No NullPointerException!
}
```
Than:
```java
if (possiblyNull.equals(definitelyNotNul)) {
    // Uh oh, might have NPE
}
```

Here, I think `AuthUserAttributeKey.phoneNumber().getKeyString()` is always non null -- but what about `userAttributeKey`? 

(Same comment for `if` check above)

------

Other thought -- you could do like:
```java
List<String> codeVerifiedAttributeKeys = Arrays.asList(
    AuthUserAttributeKey.phoneNumber().getKeyString(),
    AuthUserAttributeKey.email().getKeyString()
);
return codeVerifiedAttributeKeys.contains(/* provided */ userAttributeKey);
```

4 lines instead of 10 🤷‍♂️

