Ah, there are a lot of these. Can we just move this responsibility to the `AuthUserAttributeKey.values()`, something like? Which returns a `List`?

Or, maybe:
```java
try {
    AuthUserAttributeKey.fromKey(userAttributeKey);
    return true;
} catch (IllegalArgumentException noSuchKey) {
    return false;
}
```
Then you can implement the `fromKey` as a lookup from a string

